{
  "id": "named_selective_clear",
  "description": "`cookieJar: \"api:selective_clear\"` with `clearCookies: [\"tok\"]` targets the named `api` jar and clears only the `tok` key from that jar, leaving the default jar untouched (spec \u00a715.6). Call 0 primes the `api` jar with tok=xyz. Call 1 uses `api:selective_clear` with `clearCookies: [\"tok\"]` \u2014 the outgoing Cookie header is empty (no cookies remain in the `api` jar).",
  "spec_refs": [
    "lace-spec.md \u00a73.3",
    "lace-spec.md \u00a715.6"
  ],
  "type": "execute",
  "input": {
    "source": "post(\"http://127.0.0.1:{port}/login\", { cookieJar: \"named:api\" }).expect(status: 200)\nget(\"http://127.0.0.1:{port}/after\", { cookieJar: \"api:selective_clear\", clearCookies: [\"tok\"] }).expect(status: 200)\n",
